----[ Purpose

    This plugin allows you to background collect various MikroTik information
    and store it in tables that can then be used for graphing and reporting
    purposes.

----[ Features

    Collects the following MikroTik information via snmp on a schedule
	
    1) User Information
    2) Tree Information
    3) Storage/Memory Information
    4) CPU Software Information

----[ Installation

    Install just like any other plugin, just throw it in the plugin directory.
    Then, Install and Enable it from the Plugin Management Interface.

    You must also import the Device Template located in the 'templates' directory.
    You do NOT need to move any files from within the 'templates' directory.

    IMPORTANT: You MUST install the MIKROTIK-MIB.txt into /usr/share/snmp/mibs
    
    Once this is done, you have to set some settings in Console -> Settings -> Mikrotik.
    One of those settings is to enable data collection, graph automation, and 
    collection frequencies.

----[ Possible Bugs?
   
    If you figure out this problem, see the Cacti forums!

